Five Zimbabwean nationals are due to appear in court this week for armed robbery at boutique, Haute Horligerie in Hyde Park mall.On Thursday morning a group of armed men entered the jewelry store and stole watches worth thousands of rand.The suspects fired shots before they fled from the scene but there were no injuries.Provincial Police Commissioner Deliwe De Lange confirmed that the suspects have been arrested and that they are also linked to other mall robberies.&#8220;The suspects confessed being involved in three other mall robberies, however we will be able to announce on those three very soon.TNA Reporter